In post-samurai era Japan, 1878, 292 fallen samurais are lured into a survival game where the last competitor standing claims 100 billion yen. The battleground begins at Tenryuji Temple in Kyoto, a historical hub and spiritual sanctuary, and ends in Tokyo. Only one survivor will come out of this mysterious and deadly game.

Last Samurai Standing (2025) is the new action series by Michihito Fujii, starring Junichi Okada, Yumia Fujisaki and Kaya Kiyohara.

Derry, 1962: The Hanlon family moves to the seemingly idyllic small town in the US state of Maine to start a new life. As the parents try to settle in with their young son, disturbing incidents soon begin to pile up: Children keep disappearing without a trace, and strange events terrify the residents. Meanwhile, a couple of teenagers form a fateful friendship and together discover an ancient horror lurking deep beneath the town.

It: Welcome to Derry (2025) is the new horror series starring Bill Skarsgård, James Remar and Taylour Paige.
